morning sun ( chinese : 八九点钟的太阳 ; pinyin : bā jiǔ diǎn zhōng de tàiyáng ) is a 2003 documentary film by carma hinton about the cultural revolution in china .   the film uses archival and propaganda footage from the era as well as interviews with red guard participants and victims to explore the events and effects of the cultural revolution .   in the united states , the film garnered largely positive reviews .   it won the american historical association john e. o'connor film award in 2004 and was nominated or a finalist in regards to a handful of other awards and film festivals .